The Spreadsheet Wars
We have Steve Jobs to thank for Microsoft Excel, and Microsoft Excel to tha=
nk for Apple. Spreadsheet software was the first truly killer app for the M=
ac and home PC, and the Mac=E2=80=99s graphical interface helped bring spre=
adsheets to the masses. The two propelled each others=E2=80=99 growth.=C2=
=A0=C2=A0
Excel wasn=E2=80=99t the first digital spreadsheet. When HBS student Dan Br=
icklin had to decide between doing spreadsheets for a case study by hand or=
 on the school=E2=80=99s mainframe, he, like so many entrepreneurs, realize=
d there had to be a better way. He launched VisiCalc, a =E2=80=9Cvisible ca=
lculator,=E2=80=9D in 1978. Computer Associates followed two years later in=
 1980 with SuperCalc. That same year, Mitch Kapor sold [https://email.mg2.s=
ubstack.com/c/eJxFkM2OhSAMhZ_msjQgP-KCxWzmNQxCVXIVDNQxvv1wdZJJmrZp05yez1mEO=
eXL7Kkg-aQBrx1MhLOsgAiZHAXyELxhqtVcip54IzzTUpNQhikDbDasBvMBZD_GNTiLIcX7gtJW=
ksVMViguOz71thO-GztqJ-Ad7RXV2sH06NrDB4gODPxAvlIEspoFcX_xr1f7XeM8z8aXkqGkIzs=
ojUtbHS-hYHVQu1L--mbBbSXBtLRllFPNuFRCNayRznkpRss8tSCY7bRSvdOy_iKk0-ol6Da3TT=
nGgta9Pwokm5hwTDnEua7fi91gvRfV7VDrdsSA1wDRjiv4BwQ-PG80wwwRcuXsB4uVIpMtY5rzj=
vPHeCXFOdd9ZUSqsk_1Kv6L_gKTKo1u] VisiPlot/VisiTrend to VisiCalc=E2=80=99s p=
arent company, Personal Software, for $1 million, and joined to work as a p=
roduct manager on VisiCalc.=C2=A0
In 1982, Kapor left to build a yet-to-be-named product that combined the sp=
readsheet with graphing, and somehow convinced Personal Software to carve t=
he product out of his non-compete. =E2=80=9CI am not sure why they agreed t=
o this,=E2=80=9D he wrote in an email [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJx=
FkMuOhSAMhp_msDTchQWL2cxrGC5VyVEwgGN8-2GOi0matmnT_vk_bxssudzmyLWhvzS1-wCT4K=
