yc7nEtPT1e7U7bJ9FNzz1up8ptnuCZN0G4WHRHqQfOtMCCUpHHSbbOkgiKCGKsZGxx3uHxRhTWj=
KBunLI_Sr9i_4CnSyNbQ], =E2=80=9CPerhaps they felt I lacked credibility to p=
ull off something this ambitious. If so, they underestimated me.=E2=80=9D
Kapor founded Lotus in 1982 and launched 1-2-3 in 1983. In its first year o=
f operations, Lotus did $53 million in revenue and IPO=E2=80=99d. The next =
year, it tripled revenue to $156 million. SaaS has replaced discrete sales =
as the go-to business model for software because it=E2=80=99s better for th=
e customer, generates recurring revenue, and can lead to a higher Lifetime =
Value, but no SaaS company has ever put up such big numbers as quickly as L=
otus did.
The same year Kapor founded Lotus, Bill Gates and the Microsoft gang releas=
ed its first spreadsheet software: Multiplan. It was notable for using R1C1=
 addressing (row then column) instead of A1 (the column then row we=E2=80=
=99re used to), for aiming to be the most portable spreadsheet application,=
 runnable on over 50 different computers, and not for much else.=C2=A0
Lotus 1-2-3 crushed Multiplan, and Microsoft went back to the drawing board=
 with =E2=80=9CProject Odyssey.=E2=80=9D They originally built Odyssey to b=
e a better spreadsheet than Lotus 1-2-3 on the PC, but two critical things =
happened during development that would catapult the project into a lead tha=
t it still holds today, 36 years later.=C2=A0
First, was the team=E2=80=99s motto: =E2=80=9CRecalc or die.=E2=80=9D Accor=
ding to Jeff Raikes, Mutiplan=E2=80=99s product manager and the man behind =
Office, =E2=80=9CA brilliant programmer named Doug Klunder figured out how =
to do the calculation algorithm in two dimensions simultaneously so that we=
 could recalculate even faster than Lotus 1-2-3.=E2=80=9D Klunder=E2=80=99s=
 innovation meant that instead of having to recalculate (recalc) every cell=
 every time a cell changed, Odyssey only recalculated the affected cells. T=
hat gave it a huge speed and performance advantage over 1-2-3, which create=
d the magical experience that any Excel user is familiar with: change an in=
put, and watch worksheets full of outputs respond immediately.
Second, Gates and Raikes decided that they needed to take advantage of the =
graphical interface, so they switched mid-project from building for the PC,=
 which was operated via command line interface, to building exclusively for=
 Mac.=C2=A0
Jon Devaan, who worked on Odyssey, credited Jobs=E2=80=99 machine=E2=80=99s=
 broad usability: =E2=80=9CThat was really the important thing at the time,=
 to bring software from PhD thesis mode into something that an average pers=
on could use.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
