It hasn=E2=80=99t looked back. While it=E2=80=99s difficult to break out sp=
readsheet market share today since Excel comes bundled with Office and Goog=
le=E2=80=99s Sheets comes with GSuite, Excel holds a dominant position (~80=
%+) by most estimates, with a near monopoly for more intensive use cases li=
ke financial modeling.=C2=A0
After 36 years, it=E2=80=99s hard to imagine a world without Excel. It=E2=
=80=99s likely the single application that would cause the most damage if i=
t were wiped off the face of the earth tomorrow. Many of the world=E2=80=99=
s largest companies and financial institutions rely on Excel models to run =
their businesses, and today, Excel isn=E2=80=99t just a spreadsheet softwar=
e; it=E2=80=99s a language.
Excel as a Language
Excel is the most popular programming language on earth, and most people wh=
o program in Excel don=E2=80=99t even realize they are, in fact, programmin=
g. There are an estimated 1.2 billion people who use Microsoft Office [http=
s://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxVkU2u4yAQhE8Tdrb4MRgvWLzNu4bVQDtBwRABHiu3H5=
wsRiPRSNBqqvjKQcN7Lm_zyrWRa1vb-4Um4VkjtoaFHBXLGrxhimshp4V4M3mmpSahrltB3CFE0=
8qB5HXYGBy0kNNnglIuycOA9Aphnu28LUyC3DioBXstG7Wbnb-6cPiAyaHBP1jeOSGJ5tHaq97E=
